<p><strong>Question:</strong> Who benefits from using a solution manual?</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> A solution manual can be beneficial for students who are struggling with a particular concept or problem. It can also serve as a study guide for preparing for exams or assignments. Additionally, teachers may use solution manuals to check their own solutions or as a resource for grading.</p>
<p><strong>Question:</strong> Are there any drawbacks to using a solution manual?</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> While solution manuals can be a helpful resource, it is important to use them wisely. Relying too heavily on them can discourage independent learning and lead to a false sense of understanding. Students should strive to solve problems on their own and use the solution manual as a supplemental tool when needed.</p>